&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Heritage is building the Modern Investment Office - supporting some of the most prominent families globally to achieve their capital enhancement and preservation goals.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our vision is to help clients build enduring wealth across generations by combining institutional-grade investment sourcing with personalized portfolio construction, cutting-edge technology, and deep sector expertise. We aim to make sophisticated private market opportunities and modern wealth solutions more transparent, connected, and actionable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your role&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;In our Finance Team, you will be part of a dynamic group where every contribution is deeply valued. We expect you to be involved in key projects, take responsibility, and drive results. During your internship, you will gain hands-on expertise in the following areas:&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Month-End &amp;amp; Year-End Close:&lt;/strong&gt; Support the full accounting close cycle, ensuring timely and accurate completion of all closing activities across entities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial Statements:&lt;/strong&gt; Assist in preparing monthly and annual statutory financial statements, including management of the document repository&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;VAT Returns:&lt;/strong&gt; Support the preparation and filing of VAT returns, ensuring compliance with local tax regulations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Group Consolidation:&lt;/strong&gt; Assist in consolidating accounts at the group level, including intercompany eliminations and reconciliation of group entities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Payments Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Manage and oversee the preparation of payment schedules across all entities (excluding the fund), ensuring timely and accurate processing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bank Reconciliation:&lt;/strong&gt; Conduct weekly bank reconciliations, verifying financial data and identifying discrepancies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Invoice Registration:&lt;/strong&gt; Perform weekly registration of invoices and equivalent documents, ensuring accuracy and timely recording of financial transactions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Expense Analysis:&lt;/strong&gt; Analyse business card and corporate expense data, identifying trends and anomalies and supporting management reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are looking for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;To excel in this role, a proactive approach is needed, along with a fast-learning, highly analytical mindset and confidence to work in an extensively growing environment. The ideal candidate has an eye for detail and excels at time management.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pursuing a master&#39;s degree in Accounting or a closely related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience or exposure to audit is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience in ERP systems preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills in English to seamlessly interact with A-class international stakeholders and teammates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Microsoft Excel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for our mission: Growing more than capital, Together&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Availability to start an Internship in September 2026&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we offer&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A paid internship that spans six enriching months in the heart of Milan will shape you into a well-rounded professional. The start date will be September. You will join an international team from 10+ nationalities whom you will interact with daily and at quarterly team building events.&lt;/p&gt;
