&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Heritage is a modern global investment office built by a collective of respected families and entrepreneurs with over a century of business-building experience. We provide privileged access to top-performing alternative assets, superior portfolio construction, and a technology-enabled open architecture platform connecting clients to some of the world’s most exclusive opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We believe in mastery. Our investment team brings direct experience from leading private equity and venture capital institutions, supported by a proprietary assessment methodology and one of the industry’s most comprehensive data sets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We believe in alignment. We invest alongside our clients with real skin in the game, applying the same rigorous standards used for the founding families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We believe in technology. Our advanced digital platform centralizes, tracks, and benchmarks investments across providers and asset classes, enabling better outcomes at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our leadership comes from firms such as Apax, Hg, Hellman &amp;amp; Friedman, Carlyle, Advent, Summit Partners, Goldman Sachs, JP Morgan, McKinsey, Revolut, and N26.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Investment Analyst, you will support the full investment lifecycle and work closely with the investment team to source, evaluate, and execute opportunities across Buyout, Growth, and Venture Capital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your responsibilities will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sourcing new opportunities and building relationships with entrepreneurs, fund managers, and ecosystem partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting market, financial, and commercial due diligence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building financial models and contributing to investment memoranda&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducting thematic market research and developing investment theses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assisting with portfolio monitoring and follow-up analysis&lt;/li&gt;
